Validation of branching ratios for the B mesons

With these scripts one can verify the branching ratios of certain decay modes and compare them to PDG values

USAGE:

1. RUN ONE VALIDATION JOB (EvtGenValidate_B.py)
   Provide an input file and output file name for validating the data. Provide the 0/1 choice for reconstructing all or only most frequent decay modes on the generator level
   - basf2 EvtGenValidate_B.py input.root output.root 1 B0
   or
   - basf2 EvtGenValidate_B.py input.root output.root 1 BP


2. RUN MULTIPLE SKIM JOBS (EvtGenValidate_BJobs.py)
   Provide an input directory for validating the data. Root files are produced in a new rootFiles/ directory. Provide the 0/1 choice for reconstructing all or only most frequent decay modes
   - basf2 EvtGenValidate_BJobs.py inputDir 1 B0

3. CREATE BRANCHING RATIO TABLES (EvtGenValidate_BrTables.C)
   - root -l EvtGenValidate_BrTable.C   # Here you are asked for the input file name and the table output format